&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;A uniform worn by some menservants and chauffeurs&amp;quot; refers to a special uniform that is often designed to indicate a person&amp;#39;s occupation or a specific role. (मेनसर्वेंट्स और चॉफर द्वारा पहने जाने वाले वर्दी )&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;An example of this can be the classic all-black suit, white shirt, and black tie uniform worn by many professional chauffeurs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;Livery&amp;#39;, perfectly fits this description. Livery is a uniform, badge, or other distinguishing insignia worn by servants or chauffeurs. (वर्दी)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;Livery&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

